fields.name: CIS 405 - Software Engineering - Spring 2019
fields.description: CIS 405 -- Software Engineering: An introduction to the creation of large, reliable software systems. Topics include: requirements and specification; formal, object-oriented, and agile methodologies; system design; validation, verification, and testing; quality, reliability, and safety; cost estimation and project metrics; management, maintenance, and reuse; software standards; software engineering tools.

fields.name: CIS 203 - COMPUTER SCIENCE II - Spring 2019
fields.description: CIS 203 -- Computer Science II: Data and mathematical structures: algorithms, basic data types, arrays, linear lists, linked lists, stacks, queues, trees. Introduction to object-oriented programming. Recursion.

fields.name: CIS 303 - ANALYSIS OF ALGORITHMS - Spring 2019
fields.description: CIS 303 -- Algorithm Analysis and Design: Analysis and design of algorithms on data structures, including algorithms for processing graphs, trees and strings. Introduction to the theory of algorithm complexity.

fields.name: CIS 410 - COMPUTER NETWORKS - Spring 2019
fields.description: CIS 410 -- Computer Networks: Digital communications, computer networks, protocol families; client-server architecture, network security.

fields.name: CIS 475 - INTRO TO CRYPTOGRAPHY - Spring 2019
fields.description: CIS 475 -- Introduction to Cryptography: Mathematical tools for modern cryptography and cryptanalysis including elementary number theory, algebra, and probability theory. Survey of contemporary cipher systems, their security and complexity. Work includes programming projects and mathematics problems appropriate for the subject and level of the student.
